description: Numbers n whose prime factors are 2 and 11.
comments: A143201(a(n)) = 10. [_Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011]Also, numbers n such that phi(n)/n = 5/11. - _Michel Marcus_, Sep 22 2012
links: Reinhard Zumkeller, Table of n, a(n) for n = 1..10000
prog: (Haskell)import Data.Set (singleton, deleteFindMin, insert)a033848 n = a033848_list !! (n-1)a033848_list = f (singleton (2*11)) where   f s = m : f (insert (2*m) $ insert (11*m) s') where     (m,s') = deleteFindMin s-- _Reinhard Zumkeller_, Sep 13 2011
